[{"id":"VR725929","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block on a horizontal surface is attached to one end of a horizontal spring, and the other end of the spring is fixed in place. The block, which is free to move in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-direction along the surface with negligible friction, oscillates in simple harmonic motion. The block’s mass is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.0 kilograms\"><math alttext=\"2.0 kilograms\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mtext>.</mtext><mn>0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>kg</mtext></math></span></span>, and its motion has an oscillation period of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.0 seconds\"><math alttext=\"2.0 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mtext>.</mtext><mn>0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>. When the block is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.30 meters\"><math alttext=\"0.30 meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0</mn><mtext>.</mtext><mn>30</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></math></span></span> from the equilibrium position, it has a speed of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.50 meters per second\"><math alttext=\"0.50 meters per second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0</mn><mtext>.</mtext><mn>50</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext><mo>/</mo><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>. What is the amplitude of the block’s motion?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR725929_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.16 meters\"><math alttext=\"0.16 meters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0</mn><mtext>.</mtext><mn>16</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m</mtext></math></span></